&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROYAL NATIONAL ORTHOPAEDIC HOSPITAL NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SENIOR FELLOW IN FOOT AND ANKLE SURGERY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal National Orthopaedic Hospital provides a comprehensive range of neuro-musculoskeletal health care ranging from complex foot &amp; ankle surgery, acute spinal injury or complex bone tumour to orthopaedic medicine, sub-specialty orthopaedic services, and specialist rehabilitation for chronic back pain sufferers. This broad range of services is unique within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of a Senior Fellow in Foot and Ankle Surgery. The successful candidate will work with all of the consultants in the foot and ankle team. The successful candidate will be actively involved with teaching and research projects within the unit. The appointee will also work closely with the multi-disciplinary team involved in the management of adults with foot and ankle disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicants must have completed the FRCS (Trauma and Orth) or equivalent and will be expected to be post CCT. The successful candidate will not be expected to participate in the on-call rota for the hospital. There is ample opportunity for participation in teaching and research projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This advert is for two Senior Fellow appointment, starting April 2021 and October 2021 for period of 6 months each.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 30th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mrs Frances Carney&lt;/strong&gt; in the foot and ankle department on &lt;strong&gt;020 8385 3017.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
